creator: craig.mcclanahan@sun.com
text:
Whenever a reference to a non-existing web application resource is specified
(i.e. what would return a 404 error if it was a static file to be served),
a javax.naming.NamingException is logged to standard output in the
FileDirContext.lookup() method.  These kinds of lookup failures will occur
regularly, and need not be logged.
